The COVID-19 outbreak in South Africa is also hurting foreign nationals who live here. Some are calling for repatriation. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - The COVID-19 outbreak in South Africa is hurting foreign nationals who live here. Many last had an income in March and many have faced retrenchments and evictions. READ: COVID-19: Zimbabwe extends lockdown They're now calling for repatriation. Norest Svosve arrived in South Africa in January to print books as an author. READ: Zimbabwe reports first coronavirus death, shuts borders But the lockdown has prevented him from grieving his daughter who died in Zimbabwe since then. Svosve says there are many other Zimbabweans who want to go back home, even though South Africa represents a greener pasture. He says he has started a movement, urging his government to intervene.